# ============================================================================
# PhotoForge AI — Environment Variables Reference
# ============================================================================
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS:
# This is the canonical reference for every environment variable this app
# needs to run. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# NEVER commit .env.local — it is gitignored for security.
#
# ARCHITECTURE CONTEXT (2026-03-24, Builder 2, BridgeSwarm pane1774):
# PhotoForge AI is a hosted AI product photo generator. Our fal.ai key lives
# here on the SERVER SIDE ONLY (Next.js API route at src/app/api/generate/).
# Users never see or provide an API key — this is a hosted service, not BYOK.
# The business model is Free (3 images/day) vs Pro ($9.90/mo, unlimited).
#
# HOW TO GET STARTED:
# 1. cp .env.example .env.local
# 2. Fill in FAL_KEY (required immediately for image generation to work)
# 3. Add Stripe vars when you're ready to enable paid plans
# 4. Deploy to Vercel: vercel env add FAL_KEY production (paste value when prompted)
# ============================================================================


# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED — Image Generation (fal.ai)
# ============================================================================
#
# FAL_KEY — Your fal.ai API key.
#
# WHERE TO GET IT:
#   1. Sign up at https://fal.ai
#   2. Go to https://fal.ai/dashboard/keys
#   3. Create a new key and copy it here.
#
# NOTE: Check /Users/ak/UserRoot/.secrets/fal-ai-key.txt on the dev Mac first —
# a key may already exist and be reusable across clone apps. Only create a new
# one if that file is missing or the key is expired.
#
# WHY WE NEED IT:
#   The /api/generate route calls fal.ai's FLUX dev image-to-image model to
#   replace/enhance product photo backgrounds. Without this key, all generation
#   requests will return HTTP 503 ("Service not configured"). The key is
#   server-side only — never exposed to the browser or bundled into the frontend.
#
# KEY FORMAT: Varies by fal.ai key type; typically a UUID or "fal-..." prefix.
#
# VERCEL DEPLOY:
#   echo "YOUR_KEY" | vercel env add FAL_KEY production
#   (Never paste in vercel.json or any committed file)
#
FAL_KEY=


# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL — Stripe Payment Integration (not yet wired in code as of 2026-03-24)
# ============================================================================
#
# These variables are placeholders for the upcoming Stripe billing gate.
# The pricing page (Free vs Pro at $9.90/mo) is already rendered in the UI,
# but the checkout flow is not yet connected to Stripe. Add these when wiring
# up the payment integration.
#
# WHERE TO GET THEM:
#   1. Log into https://dashboard.stripe.com (use buildngrowsv@gmail.com)
#   2. Go to Developers -> API Keys
#   3. Copy the Secret Key (sk_live_... for prod, sk_test_... for testing)
#   4. Copy the Publishable Key (pk_live_... for prod, pk_test_... for testing)
#
# SECURITY NOTE: STRIPE_SECRET_KEY must NEVER have a NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix.
# It is server-side only. NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY is the only
# Stripe var that is safe to expose to the browser — it is designed to be public
# (it cannot charge cards without the secret key pairing).
#
# For development, use test mode keys (sk_test_... / pk_test_...) so you
# can test payment flows without charging real cards.
#
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=


# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL — App URL (for absolute URLs, OG tags, webhooks, and sitemap)
# ============================================================================
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL — The canonical public URL of this deployment.
#
# WHY WE NEED IT:
#   Used for constructing absolute URLs in OG meta tags (social sharing
#   previews), Stripe webhook endpoint registration, sitemap.ts generation,
#   and any server-side redirect logic that needs to know its own origin.
#
# EXAMPLES:
#   Development:  http://localhost:3847  (see package.json for dev port)
#   Production:   https://ai-product-photo-generator.vercel.app
#                 or your custom domain once configured
#
# VERCEL AUTO-SETS: VERCEL_URL is auto-injected by Vercel at build time,
# but it does NOT have a protocol prefix. Setting this var explicitly gives
# us a consistent, controllable value across all environments.
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3847
